@candyleer 
Notice that there is a main content "**But I dont like change the metric meaning in different condition.**" from me and @wu-sheng.
So we chose the 1 (calls and avg response time of all calls), that means there is not need to use if to decide calls equals error calls. 

You can coded such as 
```
trends.add((int) (durationSum / calls));
```
instead of 
```
if (calls == errorCalls) {
  trends.add((int) (durationSum / calls));
} else {
  trends.add((int) ((durationSum - errorDurationSum) / (calls - errorCalls)));
}
```
